Facility 1 -- * booked Booking
A Booking called booked has A Facility. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one Facility.
A Facility has some Bookings called booked. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
When a Booking is created, its Facility must be assigned. When a Booking is deleted, its Facility is not deleted and its list of Bookings is decreased. When a Facility is deleted, its Bookings are not deleted. They are assigned to another Facility.
